gw.api.util.phone

Enum GWPhoneValidationResult

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<GWPhoneValidationResult>
      • gw.api.util.phone.GWPhoneValidationResult
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<GWPhoneValidationResult>

    public enum GWPhoneValidationResult
extends java.lang.Enum<GWPhoneValidationResult>
    This enum represents the different validation states that can be returned by the Phone Validator. The best possible result is IS_POSSIBLE since there's no actual way to validate a phone number is in use.

    INVALID The phone number is completely invalid

    INVALID_COUNTRY_CODE The phone number has an invalid country code

    IS_POSSIBLE This is a possible number.

    TOO_LONG The phone number is too long.

    TOO_SHORT The phone number is too short.
